   "source": [
    "### initialize diffraction info class\n",
    "- data: LARBED intensity\n",
    "- thickness\n",
    "- tiltx\n",
    "- tilty\n",
    "- gl\n",
    "- .dat file\n",
    "- gindex for LARBED\n",
    "- variance: actually not needed here, but required for the class\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dinfo = LARBEDDiffractionInfo(data,  1100,  0, 0, 63.646, 'si110_111_002holz.dat', gindex, varianceMaps=variance)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### region of interest parameters:\n",
    "defines the region of interest for refinement\n",
    "- rotation: relative to the xaxis set in .dat\n",
    "- gInclude: g vector to include in the refinement\n",
    "- gx: horizontal g vector"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "rotation = -112.07 +1.66\n",
    "gInclude = [(0,0,0), (1,-1,-1),(-1,1,1)]\n",
    "gx = np.array([2,-2,0])"
   ]
  },
  {

     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [

  },

   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### define a customize image filtering function for coarse refinement\n",
    "function signature:\n",
    "```python\n",
    "def filter_func(image, sim=False):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    :param image: 2D numpy array\n",
    "    :param sim: if True, the image is a simulated image, otherwise it is experimental\n",
    "    :return: 2D numpy array\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "```\n",
    "Since experimental data and simulated data have very different ranges, it might be desirable to have different filtering for them. This is supported by the `sim` parameter."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from skimage.filters import meijering\n",
    "\n",
    "def meij_filter(data, sim=False):\n",
    "    return meijering(data, sigmas=range(2, 4), black_ridges=True)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n",
      "Optimization terminated successfully;\n",
      "The returned value satisfies the termination criteria\n",
      "(using xtol = 0.001 )\n",
      "thickness: 1129.580194918737, gl: 63.646, tiltY: -0.31703060406687156, tiltX: 0.5191950472399494\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "coarse.optimizeOrientationThickness(filter=meij_filter)\n"
   ]

     "execution_count": 16,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "kv = np.linspace(300.2,301.2,100)\n",
    "template_match = []\n",
    "for v in kv:\n",
    "    template_match.append(coarse.HVTarget(v, coarse))\n",
    "coarse.HVTarget(kv[np.argmin(template_match)], coarse)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "metadata": {},
